 book asks us to question why the criminalized drug user has become such a focus of contemporary criminal justice practices. This interdisciplinary book will appeal to students, academics, and practitioners in law, social theory, criminology, criminal justice, addictions, cultural studies, sociology, and science studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrug abuse and crimezCanada. 0aDrug abuse and crime. 0aDrug abusexTreatment. 0aDrug addictionxTreatmentzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aDrug addictionxTreatment. 0aDrug addictsxLegal status, laws, etc. 0aDrug addictsxLegal status, laws, etc.zCanada. 0aDrugs of abuse. 0aSociological jurisprudence. 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485582240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774855822423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774855822/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles